invalid type: string "### Calculation:\n```\nCapital: $10,000\nMax risk per trade: 1% = $100\n\nYou want to buy Bitcoin at $50,000\nStop loss at $47,500 (5% drop)\n\nPosition size calculation:\n$100 risk √∑ 5% price drop = $2,000 position\nBuy: $2,000 worth of Bitcoin\n\nIf stopped out: Lose only $100 (1%)\nIf 20% drop: Total loss capped at $100\n```\n\n## The 2% Rule (Intermediate)\n\nˇˇˇˇˇˇˇˇˇˇˇ